data.title: Tim Beck Biography
data.text:
Tim Beck is a music composer based in Los Angeles, California. A graduate of Duquesne University, Tim recently wrote music as a staffed composer for the hit children’s series CocoMelon, which has surpassed 160+ million subscribers on YouTube and various other media outlets. Tim has also written for Dhar Mann Studios, whose content surpassed 40 billion views via YouTube, Tik Tok, Instagram, and other media. He is also an active writer for Gramoscope Music and his work can be heard on several television networks, including NBC and E! channel.

As an independent writer and film composer, Tim has written for 60+ accredited films on IMDb, including 6 feature films. Tim's original film score to the feature film ON THE BRAIN was nominated for ‘Best Musical Score for a Feature Film’ at the Idyllwild International Festival for Cinema. He also played guitar for the musical score of JEM AND THE HOLOGRAMS, a Universal Pictures major motion picture.
